3.  Document Status:

    - This document is a DRAFT repository-level RFC.
    - It is not an Internet Standards Track specification.
    - It is intended to provide security policy for this repository.

4.  Normative Language:

    - The key words "MUST", "MUST NOT", "SHOULD", and "SHOULD NOT" in this
      document SHOULD follow RFC-2119 and RFC-8174.
    - This document MUST NOT use MAY.

5.  Reporting Vulnerabilities:

    If you discover a security vulnerability within this project, please send an
    email to Richeve Bebedor at richeve.bebedor+vs-scripts@gmail.com.

6.  Policy:

    All security vulnerabilities will be promptly addressed.
    We maintain a proactive stance on the security of
    the install-node-version script and related assets.

